title: [android] Returned stored PwoMetadata to clients
message:
[android] Returned stored PwoMetadata to clients

Currently, when the Fragment refreshes, we hand it newly discovered
PwoMetadata objects.  However, because the service (typically) already
has the UrlMetadata and the icon, this can prevent the fragment from
being subscribed to the UrlMetadata on refresh.  Instead of giving the
client the newly discovered PwoMetadata objects, we give it the stored
one that matches the url of the newly discovered one.

   fetch icons if we already have the url metadata, but no icon.

title: [android] Use the DiscoveryService in the fragment
message:
[android] Use the DiscoveryService in the fragment

Instead of doing scanning independently in these two different classes,
we connect the NearbyBeaconFragment to the PwoDiscoveryService and
request PWOs through it.

This additionally means that we don't need to worry about coordinating
two scanners in the MainActivity.

What this change does not do is persist PWOs beyond the 10 second run
time of the discovery service.  That may be coming in a future change.

title: [android] Fine-tune url display behavior
message:
[android] Fine-tune url display behavior

Previous behavior:

- 3s:   sort and show all urls, stop scanning

New behavior:

- 2s:   sort and show all urls
- 5s:   sort and show all new urls beneath the first set
- 5+s:  show each new url at bottom of list
- 10s:  stop scanning

already in the desired state.  This change turns our
start/stopScanning methods into safe methods that check the state of
the scanner before performing the operation.

Currently the rank is set to the signal path loss, but may include other

will be sorted on the server automatically.  However, this rank value is
useful for merging separate replies from multiple independant metadata
requests on the client.

title: Make all UriBeacon notifications public on Lollipop
message:
Make all UriBeacon notifications public on Lollipop

There doesn't seem to be any reason why public beacons would give
anything other than public notifications.  This change makes beacons
publicly visible on the Android 5.0 lock screen when the user has
"hide sensitive notification content" selected.

However, this change keeps urls discovered through mdns or ssdp as
private.

title: notification ux improvements
message:
notification ux improvements

Currently if two or more beacons exist, two notifications are created
plus a summary notification. The creation order was backwards so that
the two notifications would be created and then the summary. This made
two notification appear and then collapse into the summary. Here we
make the summary first, so the two notifications are not shown first.

title: slow metadata response fix
message:
slow metadata response fix

After scan timeout of 3 seconds, list items that do not have metadata
are shown with just the advertised beacon url. As the metadata is
received (after the 3 seconds), the correlate list item ui is updated
to show that metadata. Also, view recycling is now handled so that list
items are always cleared in getView() before updating (since a recycled
view may contain another url’s metadata from a previous cycle)

title: Remove jitter
message:
Remove jitter

Increase the "lost" timeout from 5 seconds to 120 seconds to reduce jitter. Entries are removed from the list after this number of seconds. 

The far region is now alphabetically sorted so beacons like "About" sorts high even though it is far away... and if it isn't heard in 1 or 2 cycles (5 seconds) it disappears from the list and causes visual jitter.

title: MainActivity Code Inspection and cleanup

Collapse calls A->B->C to A->B.
Use onPause/onResume to resume and pause the Scan Service.

title: Fix one source of config disconnect problem
message:
Fix one source of config disconnect problem

The MainActivity is using a fragment stack on a container for About and
Config but a different stack on a different container for
NearbyDevices. The result is a missing onPause call when entering
BeaconConfigFragment. This kept the BLE scan running at LOW_LATENCY.
Scanning and GATT connections cannot occur at the same time so this was
causing a problem.
